headlines.description: — Paolo Banchero had 22 points and 10 rebounds, Wendell Carter Jr. added 20 points and 12 rebounds and the Orlando Magic took advantage of Charlotte's poor foul shooting to beat the Hornets 119-113 Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Banchero, Magic win as Hornets struggle from foul line

headlines.description: — Darius Garland scored 24 points, Isaac Okoro added 20 and the Cleveland Cavaliers made 15 3-pointers Sunday in a 122-103 rout of the Indiana Pacers.
headlines.shortLinkText: Garland leads hot-shooting Cavs to 122-103 win over Pacers

headlines.description: — Julius Randle had 24 points, nine rebounds and seven assists, Jalen Brunson scored 21 points and the New York Knicks overcame an early 21-point deficit to beat the Philadelphia 76ers 108-97 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Knicks rally from 21 points down, beat 76ers 108-97

headlines.description: — Pascal Siakam scored 19 points, including a pair of free throws with 9 seconds left, and the Toronto Raptors rallied from a 15-point deficit to beat the Memphis Grizzlies 106-103 on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Siakam, Raptors rally past Grizzlies 106-103 as Morant sits

headlines.description: — D’Angelo Russell had 14 of his 18 points in the first quarter and added 10 assists, Anthony Edwards scored 20 and the Minnesota Timberwolves cruised to a 128-98 win Sunday night against the Denver Nuggets, who were missing two-time MVP Nikola Jokic...
headlines.shortLinkText: Timberwolves cruise to 128-98 win against Jokic-less Nuggets

events.name: Sacramento Kings at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — Trey Murphy III highlighted his season-high 30-point performance with six 3-pointers — a couple from well behind the arc — and the New Orleans Pelicans overcame the absence of several starters to beat the Sacramento Kings 136-104 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Murphy scores season-high 30, Pelicans top Kings 136-104
